** **   
** The role: **   
** **   
The Electrical and Instrumentation Engineer is responsible for ensuring the
quality of electrical and instrumentation engineering in capital projects. The
position is responsible for adhering to site and international standards and
specifications. The position is to carry out assigned work under the guidance
of the Engineering Superintendent, following discipline plans, project
schedules, budgets, design basis and engineering standards. They also
undertake engineering activities such as detailed design, specification
writing and checking of drawings on specific projects and review submissions
from external consultants.  
  
  
** Role Accountabilities: **   

  * Highlights to the Engineering Superintendent difficulties in complying with the above requirements. 
  * Brings to the notice of the Engineering Superintendent any changes in scope. 
  * Maintains an awareness ofother disciplines, activities and advises the Engineering Superintendent of coordination problems. 
  * Produces design calculations, reports for submittal for verification and certification as required. 
  * Coordinates with other disciplineto ensure timely verification of designs. 
  * Managing design sub-consultants (administration of subcontract purchasing is responsibility of the Project Manager). 
  * Stakeholder requirement specification (SRS). 
  * Participate in Project Morning Run meetings, 3 per week, and ensure all discipline inputs are included where required. 
  * Participate in P&E Interface and P&E Construction meetings, held weekly, and ensure all discipline requirements are understood by all participants. 
  * Ensure all discipline Project Controls Dashboard inputs are entered in a timely manner. 
  * Further development and review ofproject charters and work scopes, complete with options. 
  * Design change management, including processing PCR’s. 
  * Assist with key equipment specifications and selection. 
  * Sign off at design completion for design handover. 
  * Assist with technical feasibility studies. 
  * Engineering, detailed design, specification writing of drawings of different project gates for in-house works. 
  
  
  
** Role description: **   
· Design change management, including processing PCR’s.  
· Assist with key equipment specifications and selection.  
· Sign off at design completion for design handover.  
· Assist with technical feasibility studies.  
· Engineering, detailed design, specification writing, and checking of
drawings at the different project gates for in-house works.  
· Participate in deliverability/ constructability assessment and technical
feasibility reviews (HAZARD Study #2, #3)  
· Run Safety in Design workshops and implement actions.  
· Consider inputs and feedback from Construction Supplier  
· Consider inputs and feedback from Operations team.  
· Ensures that design calculations and all engineering related correspondence
are collected, indexed, and properly filed.  
· Engineering statutory compliance auditing and solution.  
· Review of designs provided by the Engineering Suppliers.  
· Engineering suppliers’ technical due diligence  
· Facilitate design gates approvals.  
· Quality management of engineering deliverables.  
· Attendance to Contractor’s Safety in Design workshop  
· Establish uniform engineering and technical criteria, methods, processes.  
  
** **   
** Qualifications (Essential and desirable): **   
Tertiary qualification in an Engineering  
